This paper involves the use of deep neural networks for automatic sleep staging, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) for this task. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data and signal processing (cs.SD) techniques for sleep studies.
